    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Voice Domain Preference encoding mismatch in Attach Request\n\n### Summary\nThe `encode_voice_domain_preference_and_ue_usage_setting` function in the NAS IEs was producing incorrect bit patterns due to a mismatch between the structure's bit field layout and the manual bit manipulation in the encoding logic. This caused the encoded IE to have the UE usage setting and voice domain preference fields in wrong bit positions, leading to failed Attach Request procedures when the network expected properly formatted IEs.\n\nThe issue was that the original structure defined a single 5-bit spare field, but the 3GPP TS 24.301 specification requires the IE to have spare bits distributed around the meaningful fields. The encode function was manually shifting bits without accounting for the actual memory layout of the structure.\n\nThis fix restructures the bit fields to match the 3GPP specification and updates both encode/decode functions to correctly handle the bit positions.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/VoiceDomainPreferenceAndUeUsageSetting.h`: Split the single spare field into two fields (spare1:2 and spare2:3) to match the 3GPP bit layout\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/VoiceDomainPreferenceAndUeUsageSetting.c`: Updated encode function to correctly map each field to its proper bit position and decode function to extract fields from correct positions\n\nTo reproduce the issue, attempt an Attach Request procedure with voice domain preference IE included. Before this fix, the encoded byte would have incorrect bit patterns, causing the AMF to reject the IE or misinterpret the UE's voice capabilities. After this fix, the IE is properly formatted according to specification.\n"
}